title: Republicans Gain Ground in Push to Take House as Democrats Hold Off Red Wave
description: The Senate remained too close to call and Republicans picked up momentum in their drive for the House majority, but Democrats held crucial seats, dashing projections of a blood bath.
dc:creator: Catie Edmondson

media:content.media:credit: Kenny Holston for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Early returns Tuesday showed a mixed picture as the two main parties battled for control of Congress.
